    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "bbox": [
        15,
        657,
        580,
        765
      ],
      "content": "The primary product, Zytiga, recorded an impressive revenue of $1.2M, reflecting a year-over-year change of 10.5%, which corresponds to a substantial market share of 35.2%. This growth can be largely attributed to robust demand and expanded indications within the oncology landscape. Additionally, Imfinzi, another critical player in the oncology portfolio, showed promise as a key oncology drug, contributing to the overall growth strategy with a growth driver index of 8.3, further enhancing the company's position in the competitive oncology market. The combination of these products and their growth drivers indicates a strategic focus on maximizing market potential and addressing patient needs across the Asia-Pacific region, resulting in a solid performance for the fiscal year.",
